description: In a room resembling a hunter's study with a fireplace, a man sits in an armchair, holding a staff. Mounted on the wall are hunting trophies, but instead of animal heads, they are disembodied feet, including a large foot with an eye, a clawed paw, a bird's talon, and a duck's webbed foot. A sign on a shelf identifies the man as a podiatrist, creating an absurd and darkly humorous scene where a foot doctor hunts and mounts the feet of creatures.
